the generality of the area laws, the present results are expected to hold for a variety of other systems. These ï¬ndings, besides showing novel aspects of entanglement in many-body systems, are of relevance from an application-oriented perspective. As shown here, quantum correlations emerge â€˜â€˜graduallyâ€™â€™ in a many-body system: starting at high temperatures in a classically correlated scenario, the system passes through a regime where quantum correlations start to be present, but in a bound form. Then, for lower temperatures, the system enters a truly quantum correlated regime where free distillable entanglement is present and potentially available for quantum information applications.
